(16,'Isolde Murphy','murphyis@tcd.ie','0032492945946','Belgium','Dear Namgyal Zangbu Sherpa,\r\n\r\nI got your details from Adrian Nelhams at ISM- I\'ve been climbing with them twice in the Alps and was looking for a recommendation for my first time in Nepal!\r\n\r\nI will arrive on 3 April and am looking for a trip of about 21-22 days maximum, to experience a mixture of hiking and mountaineering. I would have liked to do Kyajo Ri, but I don\'t think I am fit enough- so instead I was looking at Machermo (via Goyko), Lobuche E, Tharpa Chuli or Larkya. I see you have a trip to Island Peak, but I was hoping to do something a little bit quieter. Do you have any other trips?\r\n\r\nMany Thanks!\r\n\r\nIsolde','2019-04-03','22 days max','1','0','Standard','','2019-03-12 03:45:22'),
(17,'Raphael Cheminaud','andenpost@outlook.fr','0621741214','France','Bonjour!\r\nAvec une amie nous projetons de voyager au Laos en novembre 2019. \r\nNous serons 2 pour sûr et peut être 4 si on arrive à convaincre le reste du groupe.\r\n\r\nNous voulons rester 3 semaines et découvrir absolument tout ce qu\'il faut, les quelques grands sites incontournables et hors des sentiers battus. \r\n\r\nActivités : Trek, découverte d\'éléphants, nuit insolite dans un parc naturel ou une cabane, rafting etc..\r\nRythme : Nous avons 24 ans donc aucun soucis pour un trek vraiment sportif ou d\'autres activités intenses.\r\nHôtel : 2-3 étoiles, économique avec piscine de temps en temps si c\'est possible\r\nGuide : pas de guide sauf quand obligatoire\r\nBudget : 1000€ par personne\r\nDates : arrivée début novembre\r\n\r\nS\'il vous plaît merci de nous faire un prix :\r\n- Avec et sans hébergement\r\n- Pour 2 et 4 personnes\r\n\r\nMerci d\'avance!','2019-11-08','3 semaines','2','0','Standard','','2019-04-20 14:31:26'),
(18,'Francois Morin','environnement@gmail.com','','Canada','Namaste,\r\n\r\nA friend and me are beggining to look into the possibilities for a trek in Nepal in late september 2020. We just completed the Manaslu circuit last October and next time we want to explore the Khumbu sector, many have told us about the Gokyo sector as beautiful. We want to avoid the EBC as much as possible, not fans of large crowds. We are looking for a trek that will implies around 17 or 18 days total in Nepal , since we already know KTM , we do not intend of spending much time there.','2020-09-23','18','2','','Standard','','2019-05-27 15:46:07'),
(19,'Paul Wang','paul.cw.wang@gmail.com','+41797463825','Switzerland','Dear Madam, Sir,\r\nA friend of Thierry Francou has provided your contact details and mentioned that you are providing warm and excellent support during his treks.\r\nI\'m interested in doing an easy (not more than 3500m) between 1.11 and 4.11.2019 next week with you. I am arriving in KTM on 31.10.2019. \r\nWould appreciate if you let me know how, what to expect in terms of difficulties and also what to bring. I am in relative good physical conditions, running triathlons and half-marathons and I sometimes have low blood pressure and sea sickness. Last time, went to Lake Titicaca at 4000m, didn\'t sleep enough therefore a bit of sea sickness but also didn\'t take any altitude pill beforehand. A 2-day trek to Machu Piccu was perfect. \r\nThanks a lot. And looking forward to meeting you and to your recommendations. Paul ','','4','1','','Standard','','2019-10-24 22:16:16'),
