e, Pokhara International Mountain Museum</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#696969\">&nbsp;&nbsp; Convenor, Discipline committee</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#696969\">1<sup>st</sup> Vice President, Nepal Mountaineering Association (2005 -2008)</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#696969\">&nbsp;&nbsp; Convener International Mountaineer&rsquo;s Memorial</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#696969\">Life Member , National Human Rights Foundation</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#696969\">Life Member, Nepal Thailand Friendship Association</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#696969\">Life Member, J. P. Foundation</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#696969\">Everest Foundation &ndash; Life member</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#696969\">Patron and Life member of &ldquo; Sherpa Sewa Kendra&rdquo;</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#696969\">Member &ndash; Khumjung Secondary High School Management Committee</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#696969\">Advisor &ndash; Khumjung Gomba Management Committee</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#696969\">Member, Nepal Women Millennium Everest Expedition Spring 2000</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#696969\">Executive Member, Nepal Trekking Agents Association (1992 &ndash;1998)</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#696969\">Executive member Nepal Mountaineering Association (1999 &ndash; 2001)</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#696969\">Ex Vice President of Union of Asian Alpine Association (2008-2013)</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#696969\">Executive Member for Kalapathar cabinet meeting (2009)</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#696969\">President, Nepal Mountaineering Association ( 2009-2013)</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><a href=\"https://www.google.com.np/url?sa=t&amp;rct=j&amp;q=&amp;esrc=s&amp;source=web&amp;cd=1&amp;cad=rja&amp;uact=8&amp;ved=0ahUKEwiH4Z_Fo8_XAhWLMI8KHTrMDQIQFggkMAA&amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.theuiaa.org%2F&amp;usg=AOvVaw0P8otUeCTTeFc2hB6J_YZq\"><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"color:#808080\"><span style=\"background-color:#FFFFFF\">UIAA &ndash; International Climbing and Mountaineering Federation</span></span></span></a>&nbsp;(2016 - present)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','2016-12-21 14:37:53','admin','2017-11-21 09:20:31','admin'),
(2,'NAMGYAL SHERPA','OPERATIONS','1705241495598692.jpg','','1','<p><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:times new roman,times,serif\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">NAMGYAL ZANGBU SHERPA<br />\r\nManaging Director</span></span></strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"color:#696969\"><span style=\"font-family:times new roman,times,serif\">The&nbsp;Managing Director of the company, Namgyal has always grown up among stories of mountaineering and trekking exploits of his Father and grandfather.It was quite naturalfor him to follow in the footsteps of his illustrious father. An avid traveler, trekking has always been a serious occupation for him. After graduating in tourism and business management from Australia, he joined his father in the capacity of Manager of the company, a position he holds presently. He has traveled extensively all over the country and has in depth knowledge on the Himalayas. He looks after the overall aspect of the company. He speaks English, Hindi and his native Sherpa language fluently.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n','2016-12-21 14:39:34','admin','2017-05-24 04:23:02','admin'),
(3,'Laurent Rousseau','Manager','1802071518000956.jpg','','','<p><span style=\"color:#000000\"><strong>LAURENT<br />\r\nOperations</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"color:#696969\"><span style=\"font-family:times new roman,times,serif\">After studying computer science in the field of management, he worked freelance for over 20 years in this sector. At the same time, he practiced assiduously hiking, climbing and mountaineering in France and became a climbing and hiking instructor in 1982. From the mid-1990s, he regularly visited Nepal and indulged in his passion for the mountains. Now based in Kathmandu, he corresponds between our clients and the Khumbi-ila team in Nepal. Working as a Tour leader during the season, he also looks after the management of KSP, an association to improve and help the people involved in the mountaineering</span></span></span></p>\r\n','2016-12-22 14:27:56','admin','2018-02-07 11:10:56','admin'),
(7,'Jean Christophe GUERIN','Marketing & Development manager','1705241495598655.jpg','','','<p><span style=\"color:#000000\"><strong>Jean Christophe GUERIN</strong></span><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#000000\"><strong>Marketing &amp; Development manager</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#696969\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:times new roman,times,serif\">It just took one trip for him, 20 years ago,&nbsp;to fall in love with the mighty Himalayas. His first experience - a trek in the Annapurna&nbsp;Sanctuary Base Camp. &nbsp;Since then Jean Christophe is back to the himalayas year after year to explore new areas in&nbsp;Nepal, and also India in places like&nbsp;Garwahl, Ladakh &amp; Kashmir.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#696969\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:times new roman,times,serif\">After 20 years in the travel industry in Europe, Jean christophe joined the&nbsp;khumbila team, his second family in Nepal, as a marketing &amp; development manager.</span></span></span></p>\r\n','2017-05-24 09:49:15','admin','2017-05-24 04:24:58','admin'),
(10,'JOAO GARCIA','Travel Planner','1705241495598821.jpg','','','<p><strong><a href=\"http://www.khumbi-ila.com/www.joaogarcia.com\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">JOAO GARCIA</span></a></strong><br />\r\n<strong><strong>Travel Planner</strong></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#696969\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:times new roman,times,serif\">A Portuguese national and an ardent mountain lover; strange it may seem for person from this Iberian nation to be passionate about climbing. But he is just that, and he has been climbing since the last two decades and is a qualified sports technician in climbing from High Mountaineering School in Spain and Belgium, both recognized by UIAA. He leads various groups in climbs throughout the world mainly in the Andes, Alaska, the Atlas and the Himalayan peaks where he has climbed and trekked extensively. He has several successful ascents to his credit including Cho Oyu, Gasherbrum II and Mount Everest, all without bottled oxygen and unassisted, making him the first Portuguese to achieve this feat. He has been accorded several awards and has published many books on mountaineering, the most prominent among them being &ldquo;A Mais Alta Solid&atilde;o&rdquo;, which is already in its 7th edition. He has received the &ldquo;Fair Play&rdquo; award for the year 1999, by deliberation of the Executive commission of the Portuguese Olympic Committee and was acknowledged as the &ldquo;sports man of the year&rdquo; by the Portuguese Sports Confederation.</span></span></span></p>\r\n','2017-05-24 09:52:01','admin','2017-05-24 04:26:01','admin'),
(11,'Jean Michel Jorda','Travel Planner','1705241495598863.jpg','','','<p><strong><a href=\"http://www.khumbi-ila.com/www.jeanmicheljorda.fr\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">Jean Michel Jorda</span></a></strong><br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#000000\"><strong><strong>Travel Planner</strong></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-family:times new roman,times,serif\">He traveled around the world for many years on inaccessible ways to meet people. He leaves on an adventure, guided by events and encounters. Thus, he has traveled the Nepalese Himalayas, rallying the foothills of Kanchenjunga to Mount Ka&iuml;lash in Tibet, crossed the Cordillera of Peru, the Mongolian steppes or the large area of Nunavik. Jean-Michel Jorda likes people who speak about their territories. He tries to be a link through his documentaries.</span></span></p>\r\n','2017-05-24 09:52:43','admin','2017-05-24 04:25:35','admin');
